\pard\f1\b0\fi-1020\li3620\fc0\cf0 - 
\f0\b setChannel:
\b0\i (int)chan\

\fs16 \

\pard\tx3120\tx3620\tx4120\i0\fs28\li2620\fc0\cf0 Sets the channel to which the Out1nUG sends its output.   
\i chan 
\i0 is 0-based.   For example, in a square quadraphonic configuration, the channels would be as follows:\
\

\pard\tx3120\tx3620\tx7220\li2620\fc0\cf0 	
\i\ul chan
\i0\ulnone 	
\i\ul position
\i0\ulnone \
	0		left front\
	1		right front\
	2		right rear (or left rear, if using "Z" convention)\
	3		left rear (or right rear, if using "Z" convention)\
\
You should never set 
\i chan 
\i0 greater than or equal to the number of output channels.  
